namedLocations.description: The United States of America (commonly referred to as the United States, U.S., USA, or America), is a federal republic composed of 50 states, a federal district of Washington, D,C., five major territories, and various possessions. The 48 contiguous states and Washington, D.C., are in central North America between Canada and Mexico.
namedLocations.name: United States

namedLocations.description: A ZIP Code is a postal code used by the United States Postal Service (USPS) in a system it introduced in 1963. The term ZIP is an acronym for Zone Improvement Plan; it was chosen to suggest that the mail travels more efficiently and quickly (zipping along) when senders use the code in the postal address. The basic format consists of five digits. An extended ZIP+4 code was introduced in 1983 which includes the five digits of the ZIP Code, followed by a hyphen and four additional digits that reference a more specific location.
namedLocations.name: ZIP Code

namedLocations.description: Texas (/ˈtɛksəs/, locally /ˈtɛksɪz/; Spanish: Texas or Tejas, [ˈtexas] ) is the second largest state in the United States by both area and population. Geographically located in the South Central region of the country, Texas shares borders with the U.S. states of Louisiana to the east, Arkansas to the northeast, Oklahoma to the north, New Mexico to the west, and the Mexican states of Chihuahua, Coahuila, Nuevo León, and Tamaulipas to the southwest, and has a coastline with the Gulf of Mexico to the southeast.
namedLocations.name: Texas

namedLocations.description: North Dakota ( /- dəˈkoʊtə/ ) is a U.S. state in the midwestern and northern regions of the United States. It is the nineteenth largest in area, the fourth smallest by population, and the fourth most sparsely populated state. North Dakota was admitted to the Union on November 2, 1889, along with its neighboring state, South Dakota. Its capital is Bismarck, and its largest city is Fargo.

namedLocations.description: New Jersey is a state in the Mid-Atlantic region of the United States. It is a peninsula, bordered on the north and east by the state of New York; on the east, southeast, and south by the Atlantic Ocean; on the west by the Delaware River and Pennsylvania; and on the southwest by the Delaware Bay and Delaware. New Jersey is the fourth-smallest state by area but the 11th-most populous, with 9 million residents as of 2017, making it the most densely populated of the 50 U.S. states with its biggest city being Newark. transcript.text: Hello everyone, I'm going to talk about how not having advanced shipping configurations in our online storefront can affect your growth and profitability.
One of the major challenge PSP face today is not able to launch new pin products and offer highly personalized shipping options.
They lose money and customers due to their system estimate the wrong shipping cost and they are not able to integrate preferred shipping gateways.
Many PS, PS offering local pickup have challenges setting up the limited geography in their online platform.
Shipment gets returned due to wrong address which impacts their brand image and trust.

And many printers serving large corporate and franchise network have to invest and set up multiple web to win platform because their corporate customers need third party shipping and unique ordering needs.
Majority of print companies are not able to offer their key products online and launch new product segment due to challenges in the shipping in their current platform.
We would like to share a case study of large commercial printer who achieved highest sale during pandemic and today they are managing 100% orders online for B2BB2C and pre seller customer.
As they started growing, they also face challenges and the need was to launch new print products and engage customers who had unique shipping needs.
But they hit the wall as their existing platform did not have the flexibility to integrate and offer and customer multiple shipping options.
They could not configure custom size wide format products and calculate shipping cost for custom packaging.
And after implementing on print shop, within six months they saved huge money in auto processing.

Today their online storefront have seamless connections with multiple shipping APIs like UPS, FedEx ship station with instant shipping estimation, label generation, address validation and auto e-mail SMS tracking updates.

The system automatically calculates and offer most accurate and best shipping rates to the customers using shipping package master and innovative dynamic box generation logic which creates custom box with minimum wastage.
They're able to offer personalized shipping options to B to C, third party shipping options to B to B, and blind shipping to the resellers.
They also have a rule based shipping cost markup which allows them to define rules and adjust the markup charges by percentage and order value so their clients do not get overcharged.
Now they're having a local pickup options from their multiple print branch facilities and they're also able to define limited geography for each location.
During pandemic, their business was thriving as they could get orders 24 by 7.
They launched 2 online websites serving resellers B to B&B to C customers.
We have clients today who evaluated 36 different web to print applications before selecting on print shop.
And in spite of pandemic, they were able to grow sales and retain existing customers by offering online print.
And they are able to quickly set up and launch new COVID products and services online.
At On Print Shop, we have print companies to grow print sales and reduce print order management cost.
We have detailed case studies how print companies have implemented shipping automation and saved huge cost in auto processing.
Contact us to know more.
